source: src/tests.rs
expression: render_command_help(&refs)
---
Start a browser session. Without arguments, launches a local browser.
With a URL argument, connects to a remote BiDi WebSocket endpoint.

If no URL is given, checks BROWSERLANE_CONNECT_URL env var before falling
back to a local browser launch.

Set BROWSERLANE_CONNECT_API_KEY to send an Authorization: Bearer header.

Usage: bl start [OPTIONS] [url]

Arguments:
  [url]
          Remote BiDi WebSocket URL to connect to (omit to launch a local browser)

Options:
      --headless
          Hide browser window (visible by default)

  -v, --verbose
          Enable debug logging

      --json
          Output as JSON

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

Examples:
  bl start
  # Start with a local browser

  bl start ws://remote:9515/session
  # Connect to a remote browser

  bl start
  # Connect using env vars (export BROWSERLANE_CONNECT_URL and BROWSERLANE_CONNECT_API_KEY first)
